9 An Act relating to election certifications; amending
26 O.S. 2021, Section 8-105, which relates to tie
10 votes; modifying procedures for selection of nominee
or electee in certain elections; providing exception
11 to applicability of certain procedures; updating
statutory language; and providing an effective date.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 26 O.S. 2021, Section 8-105, is
16 amended to read as follows:
17 Section 8-105. A. When a tie vote is certified in the
18 nomination or election of any candidate in any Runoff Primary,
19 General Election, or any Primary Election, the election board which
20 that is authorized by law to issue the certified list or certificate
21 of election shall, at a public meeting of the board and in the
22 presence of the candidates involved or their designee, if they or
23 any of them desire to be present, select the nominee or electee by
24 lot.
