3 4. The secretary shall draw, or may designate a person other
4 than the candidates, witnesses, or other person directly interested
5 in the election to draw, one paper opaque container from inside the
6 transparent container, and the name of the nominee or electee
7 appearing on the first drawn paper inside the first drawn opaque
8 container shall be declared the winner. The secretary secretary’s
9 designee shall then expose the other name or names not drawn to all
10 witnesses present; and
11 5. The meeting shall be held on a weekday, holidays excepted,
12 between the hours of 7:00 a.m. and 7:00 p.m.
13 C. When there are three (3) or more candidates and a tie for
14 first place occurs for the nomination of a candidate at a Primary
15 Election for which a Runoff Primary will be held, the names of the
16 tied candidates shall be placed on the Runoff Primary ballot.
17 D. The procedures prescribed in this section shall not apply to
18 elections of state officers pursuant to Section 5 of Article VI of
19 the Oklahoma Constitution.
20 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
